		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Why not try the ReproPak?<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.retrousb.com/product_info.php?cPath=24&amp;products_id=42">http://www.retrousb.com/product_info.ph ... ucts_id=42</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Don't forget the Ciclone.<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.retrousb.com/product_info.php?cPath=24&amp;products_id=37">http://www.retrousb.com/product_info.ph ... ucts_id=37</a><!-- m --><br /><br />As for the battery: I'd probably just solder in 2 wires: One from the board to the battery, and the other from the battery to the board. <br /><br />I'm not positive if this will work, though  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_confused.gif" alt=":?" title="Confused" /> ... But that's what I would go with..... I guess if that doesn't work, either go to NES reproducions (<!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.nesreproductions.com/">http://www.nesreproductions.com/</a><!-- m -->) or just go and get a repro cart (try TimeWalk Games if you have to).... Or simply try to find a donor board that would work.<br /><br />UPDATE: I actually found a list of donors that would work:<br /><br />Base Wars<br />Crystalis<br />Deja Vu<br />Gold Medal Challenge<br />Kirbys Adventure<br />Magician<br />Might &amp; Magic<br />Pool of Radiance<br />Shadowgate<br />Tecmo Basketball<br />Tecmo Superbowl<br />Uninvited<br />Wario Woods<br />Bill Elliot Nascar<br />Bo Jackson Baseball<br />Bugs bunny birthday blowout<br />Dracula (imagesoft)<br />felix the cat<br />gauntlet 2<br />home alone<br />image fight<br />jurassic park<br />kid klown<br />king quest 5<br />MC Kids<br />Roundball<br />Silver Surfer<br />Star Wars<br />Super Mario Bros 2<br />Super Mario Bros 3<br />Tetris 2<br />Tiny Toon workshop<br />where in time is carmen<br />where's waldo<br /><br />Like I said, some might require a separate battery connected, but they should work well (List from <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.nesreproductions.com/">http://www.nesreproductions.com/</a><!-- m -->)

		

